HACKTIVISMO ENHANCED-SOURCE SOFTWARE LICENSE AGREEMENT (HESSLA)
Version 1.1

Copyright (c) 2025 The Automated Prayer Project Contributors

PREAMBLE

This license is based on the original HESSLA created by Hacktivismo, 
a special operations group of the CULT OF THE DEAD COW (cDc).

The intent of this license is to promote the development of software 
that supports human rights and to prohibit the use of such software 
to violate human rights.

LICENSE TERMS

1. You may copy and distribute verbatim copies of this software and
   accompanying documentation, provided that the copyright notice and
   this license appear on all copies.

2. You may modify your copy of the software and distribute the 
   modifications under the terms of Section 1, provided that you also
   meet all of these conditions:

   a) You must cause the modified files to carry prominent notices
      stating that you changed the files and the date of any change.

   b) You must cause any work that you distribute or publish, that in
      whole or in part contains or is derived from this software, to be
      licensed as a whole at no charge to all third parties under the
      terms of this License.

3. HUMAN RIGHTS CLAUSE: This software may not be used, directly or 
   indirectly, to:

   a) Violate the Universal Declaration of Human Rights, particularly
      but not limited to:
      - Article 3 (right to life, liberty, and security of person)
      - Article 5 (freedom from torture or cruel treatment)
      - Article 9 (freedom from arbitrary arrest or detention)
      - Article 12 (freedom from arbitrary interference with privacy)
      - Article 18 (freedom of thought, conscience, and religion)
      - Article 19 (freedom of opinion and expression)

   b) Conduct surveillance on individuals exercising their human rights

   c) Enable censorship or restrict access to information

   d) Facilitate discrimination based on race, color, sex, language,
      religion, political opinion, national or social origin, property,
      birth, or other status

   e) Aid in the persecution of journalists, activists, whistleblowers,
      or human rights defenders

4. This software is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind,
   express or implied, including but not limited to the warranties of
   merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and noninfringement.

5. In no event shall the authors or copyright holders be liable for any
   claim, damages, or other liability arising from the use of the software.

